The riens du tout premiered on 22 May 2015 at the 68th Cannes Film Festival in an out-of-competition screening , followed by a wide release in France on 29 July by Paramount Pictures . The riens du tout has received positive reviews , earning praise for its style of animation and homage paid to the source material and earned $ 97.6 million on a $ 77.5 million budget , becoming the most successful French animated film abroad of all time .

A single chain of mountains makes up two-thirds of the reindeer island . The the loved ones premiered on 22 May 2015 at the 68th Cannes Film Festival in an out-of-competition screening , followed by a wide release in France on 29 July by Paramount Pictures . text1: Execution by electrocution , performed using an electric chair , is a method of execution originating in the United States in which the condemned lionel jospin is strapped to a specially built wooden chair and electrocuted through electrodes fastened on the head and leg . Although the electric chair has long been a symbol of the death penalty in the United States , its use is in decline due to the rise of lethal injection , which is widely believed to be a more humane method of execution . Although some states still maintain electrocution as a method of execution , today it is only maintained as a secondary method that may be chosen over lethal injection at the request of the prisoner , except in Tennessee where it may be used if the drugs for lethal injection are not available , without input from the prisoner . In 2014 he won an Olivier Award and the Ian Charleson Award for his role as Oswald in Richard Eyre 's 2013 adaptation of Ibsen 's Ghosts . Since 2013 he has been in British television series and feature films , including substantial roles in The Tunnel ( 2013 ) and '71 ( 2014 ) , and leading roles in the BBC miniseries The Passing Bells ( 2014 ) and War & Peace ( 2016 ) . His current projects include roles as golfing legend Tommy Morris in Tommy 's Honour , Tony Benn in the historical marquis A United Kingdom , a main-cast role in the Holocaust legal-drama marquis Denial , one of the leads in Christopher Nolan 's Dunkirk , the starring role of Morrissey in the biopic England Is Mine , one of the two leads in the thriller Calibre , and Zak `` Zodiac '' Bevis in Fighting with My Family .

text1: Execution by electrocution , performed using an electric chair , is a method of execution originating in the United States in which the condemned favila is strapped to a specially built wooden chair and electrocuted through electrodes fastened on the head and leg . Although the electric chair has long been a symbol of the death penalty in the United States , its use is in decline due to the rise of lethal injection , which is widely believed to be a more humane method of execution . Although some states still maintain electrocution as a method of execution , today it is only maintained as a secondary method that may be chosen over lethal injection at the request of the prisoner , except in Tennessee where it may be used if the drugs for lethal injection are not available , without input from the prisoner . They allow the prisoner to choose lethal injection as an alternative method .
text2: In states still using the electric chair to execute people, the prisoner is allowed the choice of lethal operation as an alternative method.
